prompt: \small The figure demonstrates a sample execution according to our model. We select job $j$ at time $t=1$ which gives a value $v_j$, and causes the system to be busy for $S_j$ time units. Once free, we select job $j'$ from the set of available jobs and obtain (additional) value $v_{j'}$, and so on. %Figure above is only for illustration purpose where we sequentially choose item $j$, $j'$, and $j''$ to run as server becomes free during the process.
final_latex_code:
\begin{tikzpicture}[font=\small]
  \foreach[count=\x] \txt/\shift in {Time ($t$)/0,
                                      Available Jobs/$-\shift$,
                                      Job Run/$-\shift$,
                                      Reward up to time $t$/-2*\shift}
    {\node (\txt) at (0,\x) {\txt};}

  \foreach[count=\x,evaluate={\next=int(\x+1)}] \txt in {1,/0,
                                                          [n]/0,
                                                          j/0,
                                                          v_j/0,
                                                          /0,
                                                          R_{t+\shift,S_j}/\shift,
                                                          j'/\shift,
                                                          v_j+v_{j'}/\shift,
                                                          /0,
                                                          R_{t+\shift,S_{j'}}/2*\shift,
                                                          /0,
                                                          v_j+v_{j'}+/shift*2,
                                                          \dots/0,
                                                          /0,
                                                          1+S_j+S_{j'}/3*\shift,
                                                          /0,
                                                          /0,
                                                          /0}
    {\node (\txt) at (\txt.north east)|-(\txt.south east) {\txt};
     \path (\txt.north east) ++(0,-1pt) node[anchor=north east,yshift=-4pt] {\txt};
     \path (\txt.north east) ++(0,2pt) node[anchor=south east,yshift=4pt] {\txt};
    }
\end{tikzpicture}
